==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Affricate
<hw>Af"fri*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>affricatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>affricare</ets> to rub against;
<ets>af- = ad-</ets> + <ets>fricare</ets> to rub.]</ety>
<fld>(Phon.)</fld> <def>A combination of a stop, or explosive, with an
immediately following fricative or spirant of corresponding organic
position, as <xex>pf</xex> in German <xex>Pfeffer</xex>, pepper,
<xex>z</xex> (<xex>= ts</xex>) in German <xex>Zeit</xex>,
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Affriction</ent>⟦br⟧
